<HL>
   Financing Business:
   Ramsay Health Care Inc.
</HL>
<DATE>
05/02/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   RHCI
</CO>
<LP>
   RAMSAY HEALTH CARE Inc. (New Orleans) said it completed
refinancing of $129.5 million in senior debt. The company
said it has entered into new credit agreements for $54.5
million in senior notes, $34 million in bank term debt, $31
million in letters of credit, $3 million in senior
subordinated notes and $5 million in working capital. The
balance was applied to transactions costs. The company said
$111 million will be used to repay senior bank debt, $12.5
million to buy a psychiatric hospital in DeSoto, Texas, and
$3 million to reduce the company's 13% subordinated
promissory note. The agreements are with a group of insurance
companies led by Aetna Insurance Co. and a group of banks led
by HomeFed Bank and First Union National Bank of North
Carolina.
</LP>
