   ZEELAND, Mich. -- Herman Miller Inc., an office furniture
maker, said it completed the acquisition of closely held
Meridian Inc. of Spring Lake, Mich., a metal-case goods
maker, through a stock swap valued at about $28.6 million.
   Herman Miller said it exchanged 1,380,000 of its common
shares for all of Meridian's shares outstanding.
</LP>
