   Business Brief -- Jacobs Engineering Group Inc.:
   Mutual Cooperation Accord
   Set With Maeda of Japan
</HL>
<DATE>
05/02/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   JEC J.MDA
</CO>
<LP>
   Jacobs Engineering Group Inc., Pasadena, Calif., said it
signed a mutual cooperation agreement with Maeda Corp. of
Tokyo, under which the companies will pursue engineering and
construction projects internationally.
   Initially, Jacobs and Maeda will target projects in the
U.S. A Jacobs spokesman said that neither company could
project the value of the association, but that in several
years, the agreement could produce a "substantial portion" of
both firms' business.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   In addition to construction and engineering services,
Jacobs provides environmental and hazardous-waste services.
Maeda, one of Japan's largest engineering and construction
firms, is known for its work on civil engineering projects,
factories and commercial buildings.
