<HL>
   Business Brief -- Temco National Corp.:
   Foster Medical Supply Inc.
   Of Massachusetts Buys Unit
</HL>
<DATE>
05/02/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A11
</SO>
<CO>
   TEM
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Temco National Corp., Columbus, Ohio, said it sold its
Wendt-Bristol Medical Supply division to Foster Medical
Supply Inc., Dedham, Mass., for $10 million.
   Temco said it will have a nonrecurring profit on the
transaction of about $1 million, or 19 cents a share, in the
second quarter. In addition, repayment of bank loans with the
sales proceeds will cut interest costs enough to increase
profit by 12 cents a share annually, the firm said.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Temco said it intends to concentrate on manufacture of
health care products. The division sold by Temco was a
wholesaler of medical products with annual sales of $25
million to $30 million.
   Separately, Temco said it had a 1989 loss from continuing
operations of $375,775, or eight cents a share, on revenue of
$23.4 million. In 1988, Temco earned $45,867, or three cents
a share, from continuing operations on revenue of $17.3
million. The firm had a loss in 1989 of $961,253, or 20 cents
a share, compared with a loss of $168,992, or 13 cents a
share.
